===Etymology===
First recorded in the mid-seventeenth century, being derived from the phrase, "(one's) name's sake."

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-namesake.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
'''namesake'''

#One having the same name as another.
#A person named after another person.

